On Tue, Feb 10, 2004 at 12:15:40AM -0500, Len Brown wrote:
> If the system has no MADT, then acpi_boot_init() will never call
> acpi_parse_mcfg() -- looks like that call needs to be moved up.  (And
> yes, it seems that HPET has the same problem).

Heh.  I didn't look at the preceeding code; just fixed the MCFG code
to not have the same problems as it ;-)

That whole section of acpi boot is pretty scruffy.  How about moving
all the apic stuff into a separate function (see patch at the end of
the message)?

> I see i386 and ia64 updates -- are they the only platforms that will
> support pci-express?

They're the only platforms I have information about how to access PCI
extended config space.  Other platforms can catch up (or if people want
to send me patches, I'll integrate them with this patch).

